main event: A report concerning a UFO sighting over St Petersburg, Florida on 20 September 1963 was submitted, but the details are questionable and deemed not an actual observation.
interesting points: The sighting was described as an object slightly elongated and 30 to 50 times larger than a star,The object was traveling at a speed estimated to be 2-3 times that of the Echo Satellite,It made a maneuver from an easterly heading to a reciprocal heading, where its speed increased to approximately 700-800 mph,The observation lasted 3 minutes but the descriptions were considered inconsistent and lacking detail, and the report includes the perspective of qualified observers from a nearby institution.
witness description: qualified observers from the University of Florida Institute of Technology with relevant experience
